]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:American people of Colombian descent]]\n[[Category:American people of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:Male actors of Italian descent]]\n[[Category:American male voice actors]]\n[[Category:Musicians from New Jersey]]\n[[Category:People from Paramus, New Jersey]]\n[[Category:21st-century American singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Matt Hunter\n| image               = [[File:Matt Hunter Black & White.jpg|260px]]\n| image_size          = \n| alt                 = \n| caption             = Hunter in 2012\n| background          = solo_singer\n| birth_name          = Matthew Alexander Hunter Correa\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1998|02|20}}\n| birth_place         = [[New York City]], [[New York (state)|New York]], U.S.\n| genre               = {{hlist|[[Latin pop]]|[[Contemporary R&B|R&B]]}}\n| occupation          = {{hlist|Singer|songwriter|voice actor}}\n| instrument          = {{hlist|[[Singing|Vocals]]|[[piano]]|[[guitar]]}}\n| years_active        = 2009\u2013present\n| label               = \n| associated_acts     = \n| website             = {{URL|matthunterworld.com}}\n}}\n'''Matthew Alexander Hunter Correa''' (born February 20, 1998), better known as '''Matt Hunter''', is a Colombian-Italian-American singer, songwriter and voice actor.<ref>[http://www.sexenio.com.mx/articulo.php?id=28449 Sexenio: Matt Hunter y Karol Jes\u00fas ganan fama en Twitter] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n==Early life and education==\nHunter was born in [[New York City]],<ref name=\"latinopost081413\">[http://www.latinospost.com/articles/25574/20130814/matt-hunter-latino-justin-bieber-looks-mainstream-success.htm \"Matt Hunter, the 'Latino Justin Bieber,' Looks for Mainstream Success in US,\"] ''Latino Post'', August 14, 2013.</ref> and raised in [[Paramus, New Jersey]].<ref name=\"jrosen\">Jody Rosen, [http://www.billboard.com/articles/news/cover-story/7340769/marc-anthony-billboard-cover-magnus-media-career-donald-trump \"Inside Marc Anthony's New Latin Entertainment Empire: 'It Was Born Out of F\u2014king Frustration',\"] ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'', April 21, 2016.</ref><ref>Jordan, Chris. [https://www.northjersey.com/story/entertainment/2019/07/29/how-paramus-njs-matt-hunter-became-latin-music-star/1274821001/ \"From Paramus to the world: How Matt Hunter became a Latin music star\"], ''[[The Record (Bergen County)]]'', July 29, 2019. Accessed July 30, 2019. \"Meet Matt Hunter, a contemplative 21-year-old from Paramus who makes them scream in Colombia, Mexico, Chile and beyond.\"</ref> His mother is Colombian,<ref name=\"carreola\">Cristina Arreola, [http://www.latina.com/entertainment/buzz/matt-hunter-new-music-latino-pop-star \"Matt Hunter Talks New Music, Celeb Crushes & Latin American Tour,\"] ''Latina'', September 18, 2013.</ref> and his father is Italian.<ref name=\"latinopost081413\"/>\n\n==Career==\n===Music===\nHunter worked in voice acting from ages 9 to 12, at which point he began posting [[YouTube]] videos of himself playing the guitar and singing various covers, occasionally in Spanish.<ref name=\"gflores\">Griselda Flores, [http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/latin/7340849/matt-hunter-marc-anthony-protege \"Who's Up-and-Coming Latin Artist Matt Hunter?\"] ''Billboard'', April 21, 2016.</ref><ref name=\"latinopost092013\">[http://www.latinospost.com/articles/28065/20130920/matt-hunter-latino-justin-bieber-talks-heritage-music-career-future.htm \"Matt Hunter, 'Latino Justin Bieber,' Talks About Latino Heritage, Music Career and Future Plans,\"] ''Latino Post'', September 20, 2013.</ref> His videos went viral and he traveled around Latin America building his fan base in a grass roots fashion.<ref name=\"jrosen\"/> Around this time, he was dubbed the \"Latino [[Justin Bieber]]\".<ref name=huffpo>{{cite news|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/2013/08/13/matt-hunter_n_3748737.html|author=Jonathan Mu\u00f1oz|publisher=Huffington Post|title=Matt Hunter, the 'Latino Justin Bieber,' Looks For Mainstream Success In U.S.|date=August 13, 2013|accessdate=}}</ref> [[Marc Anthony]] later called Hunter \"the future\" of music.<ref name=\"gflores\"/>\n\nAt 13, Hunter released his first single, \"Mi Amor\".<ref name=huffpo/> He released follow-up singles in English and Spanish, \"Right Here, Right Now\" and \"Mi Senorita\", in 2012,<ref name=\"latinopost092013\"/> and then his EP ''Right Here, Right Now''.<ref name=\"carreola\"/><ref name=\"latinopost092013\"/> For the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], he released the songs \"Minha Mina Ta Loca\" and \"Mi Chica Esta Loca\" with [[Pitbull (rapper)|Pitbull]], in both Portuguese and Spanish versions.<ref>[http://thepulseweb.com/matt-hunter-recently-performed-his-new-single-and-his-world-cup-song-minha-mina-ta-loca/ \"Matt Hunter recently performed his new single and his World Cup Song, 'Minha Mina Ta Loca',\"] The Pulse Web, June 20, 2014.</ref><ref>Ruben Perez Jr, [http://www.entertainmentrocks.com/2014/06/matt-hunter-releases-new-single-mi-chica-esta-loca/ \"Matt Hunter Releases New Single, 'Mi Chica Esta Loca',\"] Entertainment Rocks, June 23, 2014.</ref> By 2016 he had amassed 200,000 subscribers on his [[YouTube]] channel and over 500,000 [[Twitter]] followers.<ref name=\"gflores\"/>\n  \nHunter splits his time between New York, Los Angeles, Miami, and Latin America.\n\n===Television===\nAs a voice actor, Hunter played the lead role of Diego M\u00e1rquez in two seasons of ''[[Go, Diego, Go!]]'' and played the same character in ''[[Dora the Explorer]]''.<ref>[http://entretenimiento.terra.com/musica/terra-live-music/studio/10-cosas-que-no-sabias-sobre-matt-hunter,87fb4f172644c310VgnVCM5000009ccceb0aRCRD.html Terra  Live: 10 cosas que no sab\u00edas sobre Matt Hunter] {{in lang|es}}</ref> He auditioned for the role when he was 10, recording the voice of Diego until he was 12.<ref name=huffpo/> He also released his weekly comedy webisode series ''Fuego Fridays''.<ref name=pulse>{{cite news|url=http://thepulseweb.com/matt-hunters-fuego-friday-episode-20-is-part-2-of-his-trip-to-columbia/|author=|publisher=pulseweb|title=Matt Hunter's Fuego Friday episode 20 is part 2 of his trip to Columbia|date=December 2013|accessdate=}}</ref>\n\n===Performances===\nHunter has performed live in the United States, Puerto Rico, Mexico, Spain, Chile, Brazil, Dominican Republic, Colombia, Argentina, Costa Rica and Ecuador.<ref name=\"latinopost092013\"/><ref>{{cite news|url= http://www.laopinion.com/2013/05/21/matt-hunter-se-abre-camino-con-mi-senorita/ |author=|publisher=[[La Opini\u00f3n]]|title=Matt Hunter se abre camino con \"Mi se\u00f1orita\"|date=21 May 2013|accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref> In May 2013, he headlined and sold out Chile's 12,000 seat [[Movistar Arena]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.cooperativa.cl/noticias/entretencion/musica/pop-en-espanol/matt-hunter-y-su-primer-concierto-en-chile-senti-cosas-que-no-habia-sentido/2013-05-22/010638.html |author= |publisher=[[Radio Cooperativa]]|title=Matt Hunter y su primer concierto en Chile: Sent\u00ed cosas que no hab\u00eda sentido |date=22 May 2013 |accessdate=7 June 2013}}</ref>\n\n==Awards and nominations==\nHunter was nominated for Favorite Pop Artist at the [[2013 Premios Juventud]], presented by [[Univision]].<ref name=huffpo/><ref>[http://www.vanguardia.com.mx/listadenominadosalospremiosjuventud-1736055.html  Vanguardia Mexico: Lista de nominados a los Premios Juventud  -- Mi artista pop: Dulce Mar\u00eda, Jenni Rivera, Jesse & Joy, Matt Hunter, Thal\u00eda, Justin Bieber Abundis Garcia] {{in lang|es}}</ref>\n\n== Filmography ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role !! Notes\n|-\n| 2009\u201311 || ''[[Go, Diego, Go!]]'' || Singing Diego || Main role (Seasons 4-5)\n|-\n| 2009\u201311 || ''[[Dora the Explorer]]'' || Singing Diego || Main role (Season 6)\n|}\n\n== Discography ==\n;EPs\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"